      {
        "type": "email",
        "html": "<p>Hey {first_name, \"there\"},‚Äå‚Äå‚Äå‚Äå</p><p>Here's the first of my \"paid members\" only emails. One of the things I want to do with these emails is try to push our focus outwards, towards future problems and points of inflection, and start a discussion about them now. You'll see what I mean by that if you get to the end of the piece.‚Äå‚Äå‚Äå‚Äå</p><p>It's also, frankly, something I probably wouldn't have written if I didn't have a paywall around elements of the site. The online debate that serves as the launch point for this piece is so toxic, that I am deeply disinclined to get involved in it at all, let alone mention key players on a public article.‚Äå‚Äå‚Äå‚Äå</p><p>But I think there's something interesting starting to happen here, both for good and ill. And I'd be remiss by not highlighting it for you, my lovely readers.</p><p>A warning: we'll be touching on issues around transphobia, cancel culture and more. But, as ever, this post is about the intersection of online publishing, technology and culture. I hope you find it useful.</p><p>I'm looking forward to your feedback‚Ä¶ üò¨</p>"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "I found myself, the other day, wondering what had happened to Glinner. ‚ÄúGlinner‚Äù, as some of you may be aware, was the Twitter handle of ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Graham Linehan",
